item.title: Average Green Premium on Eurozone Green Government Bonds Seen Rising
item.description: The average green premium, or “greenium”, on eurozone green government bonds has increased slightly in the past few months and now stands at 3 basis points, UniCredit Research said.

item.title: Natural Gas Slips With Israel Supply Disruption Yet to Affect Market
item.description: European natural-gas prices fell more than 2% despite worries over supply problems in the Middle East, with Goldman Sachs saying Israeli gas disruption was not impacting LNG supplies yet.

item.title: Economic Strength Supports Dollar For Now; US Retail Sales Data Key
item.description: The dollar traded firmer, although there is a risk it could start to weaken “due to fewer positive economic surprises from the U.S. in the near-term,” Danske Bank Research said ahead of the retail sales data, which could be the most significant release this week.

item.title: U.K. Wage Growth Cools
item.description: Wage growth in the U.K., excluding bonuses, was 7.8% in the three months to August, the first fall since January and easing the pressure on the BOE over its interest rate policy.

item.title: Lonza Sees Strong Full-Year But Faces Tough 2024
item.description: Lonza said its core earnings growth for 2023 will be above its previously indicated range, but cautioned its profits next year will take a hit from lost Moderna revenue.

item.title: Rolls-Royce to Cut Global Workforce
item.description: Rolls-Royce said it will axe 2,000-2,500 jobs worldwide as part of a transformation program and strategy review.

item.title: Nikkei Rises 1.2%, Led by Game, Tech Stocks
item.description: Japanese stocks ended higher, led by gains in game and tech stocks as initials fears about an escalating conflict in the Middle East ebb for now.

item.title: Baidu Says Its AI Model Now Rivals OpenAI's
item.description: China’s Baidu unveiled a new generative artificial intelligence model that it said rivals OpenAI’s ChatGPT, as part of its efforts to lead the race for AI development in the world’s second-largest economy.

item.title: Umicore Nets AESC Battery Supply Deal
item.description: Umicore signed a ten-year agreement to supply materials for the production of electric-vehicle batteries at manufacturer AESC’s U.S. sites.

item.title: Ericsson Sheds Guidance, Warns on Networks Recovery
item.description: Ericsson removed its key margin guidance beyond the fourth quarter of 2023 after warning that current uncertainties in its mobile networks business will persist into next year.

item.title: WSJ Tech Live 2023: OpenAI's Sam Altman and Meta's Chris Cox to Headline
item.description: AI’s impact on tech and entertainment to be a key focus for industry leaders.

item.title: Schwarzenegger Says Democratic and Republican Leadership Ranks Need Fresh Blood
item.description: At WSJ Tech Live, the actor and former California governor praised the U.S. backing of Israel and said his AI future is up to his children.

item.title: U.S. Efforts to Divide Russia and China Falter as Vladimir Putin Arrives in Beijing
item.description: The Russian leader’s attendance at Belt and Road summit marks his highest-profile overseas trip since being accused of war crimes in Ukraine.

item.title: Biden to Visit Israel as U.S. Push for Border Opening Stalls
item.description: The U.S. is struggling to get Americans out of the Palestinian enclave and humanitarian aid into it as Israel’s ground offensive looms.

item.title: Families in Gaza Fear for Their Lives Even After Fleeing South
item.description: More than half a million people have left the northern part of the Gaza Strip, fearful of an Israeli ground invasion.

item.title: War in the Middle East Challenges Biden's Defense Strategy
item.description: The U.S. is faced with re-establishing some of its military footprint in a region it has been trying to draw away from.

item.title: China Property Bonds Looked Cheap at 20 Cents on the Dollar. They Weren't.
item.description: Distressed-debt funds lost big after betting on a turnaround in the sector.

item.title: Russia Goes on the Offensive in Ukraine---and Suffers Heavy Losses
item.description: Moscow’s assault on Avdiivka shows how hard it is for either side to move the front line.

item.title: How 0DTE Options Took Over the Market
item.description: Traders are piling into 0DTE options—a cheap, fast, but risky way to bet on the market that offers the chance of explosive returns if those bets are correct. We’ll explain their rise and their effect on the stock market.

item.title: The U.S. won't be allowed to return to a policy of separating migrant families at the southern border for at least the next eight years under a legal settlement reached between the ACLU and the Biden administration.
